{
  "texts": [
    "4 The advent of digital medical records have enabled the proliferation and adoption of CDSS in healthcare systems worldwide.",
    "CDSS have been designed for various purposes, mostly customized towards the clinical and operational needs of health institutions and patients.",
    "CDSS can be broadly classi ed into two categories: knowledge-based and non-knowledge-based systems.",
    "Knowledge-based (KB) CDSS rely on a set of rules and associations derived from clinical guidelines or expert opinions.",
    "They function by matching patient-speci c data with a knowledge base and providing recommendations or alerts."
  ]
}